### creating new branch and switching to it 
    
    git checkout -b workspace
    Switched to a new branch 'workspace'

### pushing branch to remote repo

    git push --set-upstream origin workspace
    Warning: Permanently added 'github.com' (RSA) to the list of known hosts.
    Enumerating objects: 4, done.
    Counting objects: 100% (4/4), done.
    Delta compression using up to 8 threads
    Compressing objects: 100% (2/2), done.
    Writing objects: 100% (3/3), 292 bytes | 292.00 KiB/s, done.
    Total 3 (delta 1), reused 0 (delta 0)
    remote: Resolving deltas: 100% (1/1), completed with 1 local object.
    To github.com:nonus25/learn_python.git
    e44cc98..c63c56b  workspace -> workspace
    Branch 'workspace' set up to track remote branch 'workspace' from 'origin'.

### check ignore syntax
##### files

    git check-ignore -v *
    .gitignore:6:__*~	__test1~
    .gitignore:4:ignore_notes	ignore_notes

###### folders 
    
    git check-ignore -v learnPython/*
    .gitignore:2:learnPython/Complete-Python-*/	learnPython/Complete-Python-3-Bootcamp/
    .gitignore:2:learnPython/Complete-Python-*/	learnPython/Complete-Python-Bootcamp/
    
### create local branch to work with it

    git checkout -b local
    Switched to a new branch 'local'
    
### add change to local branch

    vim local_test
    
### check status if file there
    
    git status
    On branch local
    Untracked files:
      (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)

        local_test

    nothing added to commit but untracked files present (use "git add" to track)

### adding the file/change

    git add local_test

### commit local change (Note: no needs to push as u on local repo)
    
    git commit -m "test: local change only"
    [local ab13ba7] test: local change only
     1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)
     create mode 100644 local_test

    git status
    On branch local
    nothing to commit, working tree clean

### preparing for merge
    
    git checkout workspace
    Switched to branch 'workspace'
    Your branch is up to date with 'origin/workspace'.
    
    
    git merge local
    Updating 83fa969..ab13ba7
    Fast-forward
     local_test | 1 +
     1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)
     create mode 100644 local_test

    git status
    On branch workspace
    Your branch is ahead of 'origin/workspace' by 1 commit.
      (use "git push" to publish your local commits)

    nothing to commit, working tree clean

    git push
